The paper discusses watermarking algorithms for digital content, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and computer vision (cs.CV). The focus on imperceptibility and robustness suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of fuzzy systems and attributes such as saliency and edge-concentration suggests a connection to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
